	<b>Advantages of Travel and Expense</b>
	Travel and expense provides employees with a fast and efficient way to create, submit and approve 
	expense reports by simple travel and expense module.
	
	
	<b>Travel and Expense module will be enable the staff to:</b><ul><li>Create an expense reports for eligible reimbursements.<li>Submit expense report(s) electronically to the manager for expense approval.<li>Obtain the status of the expense report in the Travel and Expense Module.</ul>  
	
	<b>The few key changes as a result of T and E implementation are as follows:</b><ul><li>A single consistence process employee use across SCB location.<li>Online submission of expense report and approval process will reduce the turnaround time.<li>Standardized approval process.<li>All claims will be settled / credited only to the Pay roll account of the employee.<li>A provision to upload the relevant supporting documents (bills and receipts in the T and E claim on line</ul>	
				
	<b>CREATE AN EXPENSE REPORT:</b>The employee has to navigate the below path to access the Expense Report
	<b>Select Expense Report >> Create</b>A blank report get open, then start filling the details in the expense report	<b>
	The following fields are to be filled before submitting the expense report</b><ul><li><b>Report Id:</b> Upon saved or submission of report a unique number will be generated, this id should mentioned 
	   by the user for any T and E related query.
			<li><b>Description (General Information):</b> Purpose of this field explains the nature of expense incurred. This description is unique for the expense report <br>irrespective of the expense line.
			<li><b>Default Location:</b> The location where the staff is located.
			<li><b>Reference:</b> This field can be blank field.
			<li><b>Comment:</b> This field can be blank field.
			<li><b>Expense Type:</b> Expense is a drop down menu and list down the types of expense item charged, e.g., Air Travel, Train Travel, etc. employee should<br> select the appropriate expense type.
			<li><b>Expense Date:</b> Expense date should be the date on which the expenses are incurred.
			<li><b>Amount Spent:</b> Enter the actual amount spent towards such expenses
			<li><b>Payment Type:</b> The currency by default is INR.
	</ul>			
	<b>ATTACHMENT OF SUPPORTING DOCUMENTS</b>
	Attachment of supporting documents is now possible in the Travel and Expense system for the claimant and the approvers can view the same document.
	<b>Note: - Attachments must be in pdf before upload and also the name of the pdf file must be restricted to a maximum of 10 to 12 characters.</b>
				
	Then user <b><q>Submit</q></b> that report while clicking on Submit button.
	
	<b>VIEW AN EXPENSE REPORT:</b>
	The employee can view the expense report for the transactions already created and submitted in the travel and expense module with a report id and<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; status. 
	To view an expense report the following steps should be followed.
	
	Select <b>Expense Report >> View</b>
	
	<b>DELETE AN EXPENSE REPORTS:</b>
	The employee can delete the expense report which is in pending status only. Once the claim submitted for approval the user cannot delete the report. 
	
	To delete an expense report the following steps should be followed.
	
	Select <b>Expense Report >> Delete</b>
			
			
